=== test.180: INTERNAL_MEM resetcore after tiny TCM verify — stage=0 ===
Date: Mon 20 Apr 18:43:33 BST 2026

Stage 0: skip_arm=1 — download_fw_nvram: enter_download_state (read-only) + BAR2 ioread32 probe + 442KB iowrite32 fw; sleeps 100 ms, reads host resetintr from fw->data, writes NVRAM to BAR2, reads the ramsize-4 NVRAM marker, reads TCM[0x0..0x1c], looks up BCMA_CORE_INTERNAL_MEM and calls brcmf_chip_resetcore(core,0,0,0) if present, releases fw/NVRAM, returns -ENODEV.
(test.180: test.179 proved the tiny post-NVRAM TCM readback survives. This run adds only the first half of brcmf_pcie_exit_download_state — INTERNAL_MEM core lookup + brcmf_chip_resetcore(core,0,0,0) — before release/return. Still no brcmf_chip_set_active, no device-side resetintr use, no broad TCM dump, no ARM release.)

=== Pre-test BAR0 MMIO guard ===
BAR0 MMIO UR/I/O error (7ms) — device alive; SBR in probe should fix. Proceeding.

